    <item>
      <title>Why these new boards rock.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=10372#M10372</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I'm sure someone has already thanked the people behind the new boards copiously, but the thread may have gotten lost somewhere and so I want to make sure I give a shout out to the folks behind this wonderful change for the better.&amp;nbsp; Some specifics that I love:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) The Rating System.&amp;nbsp; Not only does it allow me to feel special for having a 4-star average (knock on wood), but it allows me to filter out the crap.&amp;nbsp; I have not yet exercised that option, but I love that it's there.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2) More guild-friendly.&amp;nbsp; When I asked, Brenlo was kind enough to give me permission on the old boards to put a link to my guild web site at the end of my posts.&amp;nbsp; But even that felt like I was doing this naughty, dirty thing and that Brenlo was in league with the devil for allowing it.&amp;nbsp; :smileytongue:&amp;nbsp; Now, not only can I put my guild link automatically via a signature file, but the personal profiles actually ENCOURAGE you to list your guild and give the url.&amp;nbsp; I've never understood why there was so little support for guilds by Sony before, and this is a wonderful and long-awaited attitude change.&amp;nbsp; Combine this with the EQLive community announcements, and guilds look to be completely legitimized by the Man.&amp;nbsp; Thanks!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3) Ability to communicate with people who interest you.&amp;nbsp; On the old boards if you wanted to contact a&amp;nbsp;specific person&amp;nbsp;you had to post your information for all to see and hope that the person you were trying to contact&amp;nbsp;ran across it.&amp;nbsp; I LOVE that you can now contact people directly, and not have to waste board space.&amp;nbsp; It's hard for me to resist the temptation to whisper sweet nothings in Coyote's ear, but I'll do my best.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4) Options, options, options.&amp;nbsp; Enough said.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway, thanks so much guys, and if I've left anything out that totally r0xx0rz about these new boards, someone please fill in the blanks!&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
